The collage features images from the film, specifically images of Brigitte Bardot. Â° Â° Â° Â° Â° Â° Â°Le MÃ©pris (Contempt) is a film about a woman who has grown to despise her husband. Her husband writes screenplays and is working on one for a new film about the Odyssey. The different characters in the film debate their ideas about the Odyssey while paralleling Odysseus and Penelope\'s relationship with the husband and wife. I love the idea that Odysseus didn\'t kill the suitors out of jealous rage after seeing them in his house and knowing they wanted to marry Penelope. He had told Penelope to entertain the suitors so he would not have been surprised to find them in his house. It was when he realized that Penelope despised him that he entered into a fit of rage. Killing the suitors wasn\'t an act of jealousy, it was a desperate attempt to win back Penelope\'s love. She despised his passivity. His apathy repulsed her. Only an uncontrolled and emotional act of violence could win her back. The Odysseus that Penelope loved, would never have let another man enter his house. Odysseus had to kill the man that Penelope despised.

column8: You meet people and they swear they are hard, not emotional, not open. And it\'s true in a sense. This truth has formed itself from their experiences, no denying that.
